    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Meaning "egg," refers to the distinctive domes of Indian temples and other architecture, usually hemispherical or egg-shaped; sometimes refers to other egg-shaped elements of Indian architecture. In North Indian temple architecture, a spirelet form found in the Śekharī temple superstructure.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
